{
  "text": "GPCR actions in PCa involve cell growth enhancement via ERK6, a mitogen-activated protein kinase-related serine/ threonine kinase (MAPK) [CITATION_1] . ERK can phosphorylate AR at several sites thereby upregulating AR target genes [CITATION_2] . GPCRs that signal through stimulatory G proteins α (Gsα) can also transactivate AR through cyclic adenosine monophosphate (cAMP) production [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and protein kinase A (PKA) [CITATION_5] . In addition, the activated Gsα subunit can directly activate AR and act synergistically with low androgen concentrations to increase AR activity in PCa cells [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12573098",
    "[CITATION_2]": "10996598",
